description:
Who doesn't love Wordle, the little word game that has
TAKEN the
WORLD by
STORM? We play
EVERY
day ourselves.

But Wordle isn't exactly unique.
THERE were similar
GAMES that came before. In fact, its origins can be traced back to Mastermind, a children's
BOARD game with different colored pegs. It was invented by a Romanian-born Israeli Jew, Mordecai Meirowitz, in 1970.

And Mastermind itself can TRACE its origins back to
"BULLS
 and Cows", a computer game written back in the 1960s. It used numbers, not letters or colors.

TRULY, there are no original
IDEAS left.

